In a 2-qt. microwave-safe dish, heat oil at 70% power for 2 minutes. Add the pork, soy sauce and garlic powder; toss to coat. Cover and microwave on high for 7-8 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Stir in peas and onions. Cover and microwave at 70% power for 3 minutes. Combine cornstarch and broth until smooth; stir into pork mixture. Cover and microwave on high for 2 minutes; stir. Cover and microwave 4-5 minutes longer or until thickened, stirring every minute. Serve with rice if desired.